<H2>Introduction:</H2>This lab will provide an introduction to compiling on 
csci.stcloudstate.edu and on printing the results in the ECC102 lab. 
<H2>Lab Assignment:</H2>
<OL>
  <OL>
      <LI>Create a new directory, <u><tt>lab3</tt></u>, and move to it. 
	<LI><I>run</I>: <tt><B>cp</B> ~cs201300/lab3/hello.cpp</tt> .<BR>
	<tt><B>cp</B> ~cs201300/lab3/hello1.cpp<tt> .<BR>
	<tt><B>cp</B> ~cs201300/lab3/hello2.cpp<tt> . 
    <LI>Edit the 3 files to fill in the correct information in the square 
    brackets 
    <LI>Compile each one: <B>g++</B> <I>filename</I>.cpp&nbsp; -o 
    <I>filename</I> 
    <LI>Each <I>filename</I> should be executable now.&nbsp; Confirm. 
    <LI>Run each program by typing its name.&nbsp; Redirect its output to a 
    common output file.&nbsp;<BR>Ensure that the output of the second and third 
    programs are appended to the output of the first program. 
    <LI><B>cat </B>together all three source files, followed by the output file 
    into a new single file, <u><tt>allout</tt></u> 
		    <LI>  print and hand in a copy of <u><tt>allout</tt></u>. </LI>
  </OL>
</OL>

